						               													<description>The Haunted House: Confusing Circle is a speed matching game that helps children to practice addition. &amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Collect ghosts with Shinbi&amp;rsquo;s powerful magic circle and magic dice before they disturb the peace of Shinbi Apartment!&amp;rdquo;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to Play:&amp;#10;(1) Set the board and place ten ghost cards on each side of the decagonal board.&amp;#10;(2) A player rolls two dice. Then, all players simultaneously look for the ghost cards correspond to both dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    One die tells the number of ghosts and the other one tells the number of wisps that should be on it. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;(3) After spotting the cards, add up all the number on the board where they are attached. Shout out the total!&amp;#10;(4) If the math is right, the player takes all those cards. Each card gives 1 point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
